{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17598664","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17598664"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:42:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:42:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15499"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15499"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.6,0.06,0,0.24]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8190"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65840"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8190","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8190"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15499"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51285"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6812"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19822"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19827"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65840","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65840"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EChronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) commonly leads to increased pulmonary vascular resistance and pulmonary hypertension through several mechanisms. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most significant mechanism of increased pulmonary vascular resistance in chronic obstructive pulmonary disease?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Polycythaemia","Hypoxic vasoconstriction","Inflammatory cell infiltration","Increased blood viscosity","Vascular compression from hyperinflation"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn COPD, several mechanisms contribute to increased pulmonary vascular resistance (PVR) and subsequent pulmonary hypertension. \u003Cstrong\u003EHypoxic vasoconstriction\u003C/strong\u003E is the most important mechanism. Chronic alveolar hypoxia triggers vasoconstriction of small pulmonary arteries, which initially is reversible but becomes fixed over time due to vascular remodelling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInflammatory cell infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E occurs in COPD airways and may affect vessels, but it is not the primary mechanism of increased PVR.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolycythaemia\u003C/strong\u003E can develop in response to chronic hypoxia as a compensatory mechanism to increase oxygen-carrying capacity. While it may contribute to increased blood viscosity and PVR, it is not the primary mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased blood viscosity\u003C/strong\u003E results from polycythaemia but plays a relatively minor role in increasing PVR compared to hypoxic vasoconstriction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVascular compression from hyperinflation\u003C/strong\u003E may occur in severe COPD but is not the primary mechanism of increased PVR. The effect is relatively minor compared to hypoxic vasoconstriction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these mechanisms is crucial as pulmonary hypertension in COPD is associated with increased mortality and reduced exercise capacity. Long-term oxygen therapy can help reverse hypoxic vasoconstriction and improve outcomes in patients with severe COPD.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic hypoxia leads to pulmonary vasoconstriction and vascular remodelling in COPD.","Multiple mechanisms contribute to increased pulmonary vascular resistance in COPD including hypoxic vasoconstriction, vascular remodelling, and polycythaemia.","Pulmonary hypertension is a common complication of severe COPD."],"references":["Leap J, Arshad O, Cheema T, Balaan M. Pathophysiology of COPD. Crit Care Nurs Q. 2021 Jan/Mar;44(1):2-8. doi: 10.1097/CNQ.0000000000000334. PMID: 33234854.","Spurzem JR, Rennard SI. Pathogenesis of COPD. Semin Respir Crit Care Med. 2005 Apr;26(2):142-53. doi: 10.1055/s-2005-869535. PMID: 16088433.","Brandsma CA, Van den Berge M, Hackett TL, Brusselle G, Timens W. Recent advances in chronic obstructive pulmonary disease pathogenesis: from disease mechanisms to precision medicine. J Pathol. 2020 Apr;250(5):624-635. doi: 10.1002/path.5364. Epub 2019 Dec 3. PMID: 31691283; PMCID: PMC7216938.","Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51285"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15499"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51285","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51285"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T09:22:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T09:22:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8190"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65840"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/ta